UNITED STATES of America v. Herbert George HOUSE. No. 3372. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. July 15, 1946. See also, 10 Cir., 144 F.2d 555. Cloen A. Summers, U. S. Atty., and Francis Stewart, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Muskogee, Okl., for appellant. No appearance for appellee.

Before PHILLIPS, Circuit Judge, and SYMES, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal docketed and dismissed on motion of appellant.
